## Null Safety

### Nullable Types
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD - unsafe cast
val name = (item as String?)

// ✅ GOOD - safe when expression
when (item) {
    is String -> println(item)
    else -> Unit
}

// ✅ GOOD - null-coalescing
val name = item?.name ?: "Unknown"
```

### Non-Null Assertions
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD - can throw NPE
val value = nullable!!

// ✅ GOOD - handle null explicitly
val value = nullable?.let { process(it) } ?: default
```

### Optional Parameters
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - default values instead of null
fun fetchData(id: String, limit: Int = 10) {}

// ✅ GOOD - explicit optional
fun process(item: Item?): Result<Unit> {}
```

