## Sealed Classes & Enums

### Use Sealed for Variants
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - sealed class for UI states
sealed class UiState {
    data object Loading : UiState()
    data class Data(val items: List<Item>) : UiState()
    data class Error(val message: String) : UiState()
}

// ❌ BAD - boolean flags
var isLoading: Boolean = false
var hasError: Boolean = false
var errorMessage: String? = null
```

### Pattern Matching
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - exhaustive when
when (state) {
    UiState.Loading -> showLoader()
    is UiState.Data -> showItems(state.items)
    is UiState.Error -> showError(state.message)
}

// ❌ BAD - non-exhaustive
if (state is UiState.Loading) {
    showLoader()
}
```

