## Comments

### When to Comment
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - explains non-obvious intent
// We combine local and remote to prefer cached data when offline
val items = combine(local, remote) { l, r -> r.ifEmpty { l } }

// ✅ GOOD - explains why (not what)
// Retry 3 times as network is unreliable in this region
repository.fetchWithRetry(retries = 3)

// ❌ BAD - states the obvious
// Increment counter
counter++

// ❌ BAD - redundant
// Get items from repository
val items = repository.getItems()
```

### Documentation Comments
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - KDoc for public APIs
/**
 * Fetches items from the repository and maps to UI models.
 *
 * @param query Search query string
 * @return Flow of matching items
 * @throws IllegalArgumentException if query is empty
 */
fun searchItems(query: String): Flow<List<ItemUI>>

// ✅ GOOD - complexity notes
/**
 * Performs a 3-way merge:
 * 1. Local database (cached)
 * 2. Remote API (fresh)
 * 3. Memory cache (fastest)
 *
 * Remote takes precedence if available, then local, then memory.
 */
fun fetchItemsWithCache(): Flow<List<Item>>
```

